import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Grid, Image, Segment, Header, Feed } from 'semantic-ui-react';
import MovieInfo from '../HeaderSegement/Explore/MovieInfo';
import vk from "../Images/vk.png";
import got from '../Images/got.png';
import ghost from '../Images/ghost.png';
import ImageOfRolePlayers from './Explore/ImageOfRolePlayers';



const HeaderPart = () => {

    return (
        <React.Fragment>
            <Grid columns="2" inverted>
                <Grid.Row textAlign='center' className="RowPadding">
                    <Grid.Column width={4}>
                        sds
                    </Grid.Column>
                    <Grid.Column width={12} className="headerImageBoxShadow">
                        <Image className="headerImage"
                            src={ghost}
                        />
                    </Grid.Column>
                </Grid.Row>
                <Grid.Row textAlign='center' className="RowPadding">
                    <Grid.Column width={5}>
                        f
                    </Grid.Column>
                    <Grid.Column width={11}>
                        <Grid inverted>
                            <Grid.Row textAlign='center'>
                                <Grid.Column columns="equal" width={12}>
                                    <Segment style={{ overflow: 'auto', maxHeight: 200 }}>
                                    <ImageOfRolePlayers />
                                    </Segment>
                                </Grid.Column>
                                <Grid.Column width={4}>
                                    <MovieInfo url="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3PK2tIyENVA&t=2s" />
                                </Grid.Column>
                            </Grid.Row>
                        </Grid>
                    </Grid.Column>
                </Grid.Row>
            </Grid>
        </React.Fragment>
    )
}

export default HeaderPart;
